### Fig. 3a,b - Mutual information vs common reads

df3 <- read.csv("mutual_information.GM12878_GSE77288.pairs.txt", sep = " ", header = F)
names(df3) <- c("var1", "var2", "mi", "cov", "label")

df3$label[df3$label == 1] <- 0

df3$cov_bin <- cut(df3$cov, breaks = c(0, 5, 10, 15, 20, Inf), right = F)

PAL <- brewer.pal(7, "Set2")

df4 <- df3[df3$label != 0, ]
df4c <- df4 %>%
    group_by(cov_bin, label) %>%
    summarise(n = n(), x = mean(mi), y = mean(cov)/3)

g1 <- ggplot(df4, aes(x = mi)) + geom_density(aes(color = cov_bin), size = 1, adjust = 1) + geom_text(data = df4c,
    aes(color = cov_bin, label = n, x = x, y = y)) + scale_color_manual(values = PAL[2:7]) + theme_classic()


df4 <- df3[df3$label == 0, ]
df4c <- df4 %>%
    group_by(cov_bin, label) %>%
    summarise(n = n(), x = mean(mi), y = mean(cov)/3)

g2 <- ggplot(df4, aes(x = mi)) + geom_density(aes(color = cov_bin), size = 1, adjust = 1) + geom_text(data = df4c,
    aes(color = cov_bin, label = n, x = x, y = y)) + scale_color_manual(values = PAL[2:7]) + theme_classic()

Fig. 3c - Detremining MI cutoffs

FPv = 0.9
FNv = 0.05
cov_cutoff = 10

y <- df3[df3$label == 0 & df3$cov >= cov_cutoff, ]$mi
y <- sort(y)
cumy <- ecdf(y)(y)
for (i in 1:length(cumy)) {
    if (y[i] > 0.515) {
        print(cumy[i])
        FP <- y[i]
        break
    }
}
## [1] 0.8653445
y <- df3[df3$label == 2 & df3$cov >= cov_cutoff, ]$mi
y <- sort(y)
cumy <- ecdf(y)(y)
for (i in 1:length(cumy)) {
    if (cumy[i] > FNv) {
        print(y[i])
        FN <- y[i]
        break
    }
}
## [1] 0.515
g1 <- ggplot(df3[df3$cov >= cov_cutoff & df3$label != 1, ], aes(x = mi)) + stat_ecdf(aes(color = as.factor(label)),
    size = 1, adjust = 1) + geom_vline(xintercept = FP, linetype = "dashed", color = "green") +
    geom_vline(xintercept = FN, linetype = "dashed", color = "blue") + geom_hline(yintercept = FPv,
    linetype = "dashed", color = "green") + geom_hline(yintercept = FNv, linetype = "dashed", color = "blue") +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 1, 0.1)) + scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 1, 0.1)) +
    scale_color_manual(values = c(PAL[3], PAL[5])) + theme_classic()

### Fig. 3d - Linkage event cont per cluster

df3 <- read.csv("mutual_information.GM12878_event_counts.txt", sep = " ", header = F)
names(df3) <- c("cell", "far", "close", "non_testable", "testable")
head(df3)
cell far close non_testable testable
1 5127 0 107 43
5 15060 0 404 290
10 27683 0 1052 561
15 43827 0 2090 1162
20 63927 0 3642 2182
25 88374 0 5696 3740 
df3 <- melt(df3, id.vars = c("cell"))

df4 <- df3[!df3$variable %in% c("far"), ]
df4 <- df3[df3$variable %in% c("non_testable", "testable"), ]

g1 <- ggplot(df4, aes(x = as.factor(cell), y = value, label = value)) + geom_bar(aes(fill = variable),
    color = "white", position = "dodge", stat = "identity", width = 0.8) + geom_text(aes(y = value,
    color = variable), position = "stack") + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set2") + scale_color_brewer(palette = "Set2") +
    scale_y_log10() + theme_minimal()
